name: MOCK ORDER - DEMO CASSETTE (LTD 100)
description:
New release from IMMINENT DESTRUCTION RECORDS!

6 track demo from transatlantic Hardcore Punks MOCK ORDER.

The lyrics are powered out and written by Hannah in Ireland and the music is penned and performed over in Canada by Cody.

The result is fast, catchy anarcho hardcore punk.
D.I.Y. in the truest sense.

Pro-cassette, 1st pressing, limited to 100 copies on green tape with glossy inlay with lyrics to all songs.

Sample Here: https://soundcloud.com/imminentdestruction/mock-order-sleep-anxiety

name: RIISTETYT - KORRPIEN PARAATI LP
description:
Brand new full length from RIISTETYT!

"One of the pioneers of finnish hardcore-punk is back with a devastating new album. Straight from Tampere punk city since 1981, 11 tracks of dense hardcore as the air on the darkness of finnish forests contaminated by the return of original bassist Piise. The speed and unmistakable attitude under the noise edge of one of the most memorable punk vocals in history is back to Terrotten Records after 12 years."

It's great to hear a band that's been going so long, still being able to cut it. This is classic stuff.

name: KONTRASEKT- END OF DESTRUCTION LP
description:
After last years debut 7" EP, these Minneapolis Crust Punks deliver 11 tracks of unbridled power and anger on their first full length released on VEX records.

This LP stunned me with it's ferocity and addictiveness.
This is such an improvement on last years 7"...you can tell these guys have worked tirelessly to produce something of real quality here.

Fans of FRAMTID, ENT, DOOM, DISCHARGE,SLANG etc. will love this!
No 'Epic Crust' plodders here, just sheer booming power!

One of the best LP's i've heard all year. Highly recommended!

name: FAMINE YEAR - JA KAINEN KRUUNAA KUOLEMA LP
description:
15 tracks of crushing Finnish Hardcore from FAMINE YEAR.

This is an absolute ripper of a 12" and has been highly praised since its release this month. 

This band are exploding all over Finland and beyond.

Grab this and see why.

Killer cover artwork by Vlad Von Haddock.

name: THE REALITY SHOW - LIBERATION ESCHATOLOGY LP
description:
10 track debut full length from THE REALITY SHOW.

Blazing metallic hardcore punk from Finland.

Comes housed in a nice double sided printed inner sleeve.

Limited to 300 copies only.

name: LEFT COLD - SYMPTOMS OF OUR TIME 7"
description:
Raging 4 track EP from Finland's LEFT COLD.

This is their first vinyl release after a couple of self released cassettes.

This is hardcore crust punk with some Youth Crew style breakdowns.

Better than I make it sound!

Try it out for yourself here: http://leftcold.bandcamp.com/

Limited to 205 copies.

name: HORROS - IRON BIRDS 7"
description:
Brand new 3 tack 7" from Finnish HC punks HORROS.

More metal influenced that their previous 7", this is 'Tragedy-esque'

3rd track takes up the entire side B and is an apocalyptic doom laden jam.

Limited to 300 copies only.

name: HORROS - S/T 7" (GREY VINYL)
description:
Debut 4 track EP from Finnish HC punks HORROS.

Raging hardcore punk that sounds like a cross between DOOM and KVOTERINGEN.

Limited to 170 copies on grey vinyl.

name: BETTER NOT BORN / CAUSE A RIOT -SPLIT 7" (RED VINYL)
description:
4 track split EP between two Finnish HC / Crust bands that have arisen from the dark cold nights in Helsinki.

This is pressed on red vinyl and limited to 300 copies.
Also comes with a BETTER NOT BORN patch.

Great artwork!

Review from PE:

"This record is 2 songs each from a couple bands on D.I.Y. label Filthy Rat Records based in Helsinki, Finland. BETTER NOT BORN has male vocals over rapid hardcore, with great breakdowns.  think F-Minus, or Gruk.  They have been compared with Tragedy, but I don't really see it.  a great up and coming band, their debut full length is due to be out next year (2014).  on the B-side, CAUSE A RIOT is a streetpunk style with poppy roots, much like The Unseen or the Virus.  the diversity on this split really makes it feel like two different records."

name: BETTER NOT BORN - DOWNFALL 7"
description:
4 tracks of Hardcore / Crust from Finland.

1st EP from this new band out of Helsinki.

Includes download code.
Also comes with a BETTER NOT BORN sticker.

Limited to 300 only.

Review from PE:

"BETTER NOT BORN are a Finnish five piece that play a mix of hyper d-beat and Midwest U.S. hardcore that is a lot less gloomy and desolate sounding than the artwork would have you believe. Aside from intros and breaks, these guys are high energy maniacs tat probably put on a great live show. And when you get to the last track, Freefall, it changes up a little and starts with a nice slow, melodic creepy intro that quickly gets interrupted by blast beats and chaos then settles into fast hardcore and revisits all those elements. The sound quality and mix are well executed, especially for a DIY recording from the band’s practice studio. Initially I thought this was done by an experienced label. Nice work. Hopefully they’ll work with some other bands and either show them the way or release albums for them.  It even comes with a download card. All the songs are printed in English and are of personal nature, but have sociopolitical angles. This is a killer band and I hope they release more material soon. This 7″ is a hand-numbered 300 pressing, so make sure you get a copy soon."

name: ATTACK SS / FRENZY - SPLIT 7" EP
description:
Great new split from two top bands.

ATTACK SS from Japan give three new tracks (including a DISCHARGE cover) on this, their 3rd 7" release.

FRENZY also produce three new songs as the follow up to their 2012 debut EP.

Pressed on 'neon lime green' vinyl with full colour artwork and a double sided fold out inner.

name: EN PSYCHRO / KYFFPACK - SPLIT 7"
description:
EN PSYCHRO from Cyprus finally make it to vinyl!

After a great demo in 2012 I picked up on these guys and was excited to see their debut 7" hit the streets. 
Not a household name just yet but you're sure to hear more from them in the near future as an LP is also on the way.

Production is great on this split with German crust punks KYFFPACK.

They make a good team on this split as both bands play political angry crust tinged hardcore.

Limited to 300 copies and the majority of those are gone already so pick one of these up while you can.

name: UNARM - MYTH AND REALITY 311 LP
description:
20 track crusher from Japanese HC punks UNARM.

Their last 7" was impressive and showed a progression from their early sound but this LP takes another step forward and manages to maintain the power over the course of a full length.

I'd say this was easily the bands best release to date.

Although the crasher crust elements are still present on this LP there's also shades of LIFE, AKKA, SCREW WITHIN,ABRAHAM CROSS mixed in to create a storming wave of sound with an Anarcho / protest vibe present throughout.

The title of the LP refers to the nuclear disaster in Fukushima, Japan on 3/11. 

Lyrics in Japanese / English and a separate lyric sheet in French.

name: LIPCREAM - EARLY YEARS GIG LP
description:
RESTOCKED SOON!!!!

15 track official live album for these classic 80's Japanese punks.
comes in a poster sleeve.

Grab one while they last....

name: LIPCREAM - LONELY ROCK 7" EP
description:
Official reissue of this classic 4 track EP, first released in 1984.

Original copies go for insane prices so pick up a faithful reproduction while you can!

Comes with sticker.

name: VIVISICK - RESPECT AND HATE LP (BROWN VINYL)
description:
10 track LP by Japanese Hardcore Punks VIVISICK.

Even though they have been around since the late 90's, this is their first solo full length LP release.

This is a band that has aged incredibly well and now sound better than they ever did. Before they were a bit too thrashy for my taste and I found their EP's a bit of a tough listen but here they have really nailed it and achieved a thing of beauty.
This is an album I have no trouble playing from start to finish and is definitely their best work to date.

Matched by great screened cover art with a HUGE fold out inner and pressed on brown vinyl.

name: LETHE - S/T LP
description:
New release from IMMINENT DESTRUCTION RECORDS!

9 track debut LP from LETHE.

Crushing and dark crust / hardcore from Greece.

Featuring members of DIRTY WOMBS, DALA SUN and LOCUST.

I truly believe this will be recognised as one of the top crust punk LP's of 2013.

The production is perfect, accentuating the power and complexity of the chord changes on these songs.

The artwork is by Andreas Admczeroseven (who also drew the cover for the ROAR OF INDIGNATION compilation LP) and is another piece of amazing work. 
Backed up with a 4 page fold out insert with lyrics in both Greek and English.

This is a co-release  with the follwoing labels:
SCARECROW RECORDS / NO SANCTUARY RECORDS / CENTIPEDE RECORDS / THE MUSIC WE CREATE RECORDS / EYE5 RECORDS CLEAN HEAD RECORDS

CHECK A SAMPLE TRACK HERE: https://soundcloud.com/imminentdestruction/lethe-role

name: NEMESIS - 暁鐘 / GYOU-SHOU 7"
description:
RESTOCKED!!
Brand new 4 track EP from Japanese HC warriors NEMESIS.

This tops their debut 7" in my opinion and has a slightly different sound to it, most likely a change in production.

This is raging, catchy hardcore with killer solos.

This is similar to the burning spirits style of hardcore but more driven. 
The chaos of the first 7" is still here but you can tell the band has progressed a lot since then as the song structures here seem more intricate.

JUDGEMENT, WARHEAD, are definitely good references here. 

If you liked the first 7", you'll love this!

name: VENDETTA - DESTROY / FIGHTING MAN 7" (JAPANESE TOUR EDITION)
description:
Two brand new songs from Japanese HC Punks VENDETTA!

I really think these are their best songs yet!
Definitely my favourites anyway.

This is a single sided 7" and released for the Japanese 'Doomsday Troops' tour with Swedish Punks EATER. 

Unmissable if you're a fan of this band.

Limited to 300 copies only and only a handful of these made it outside of Japan so grab one while you can.

name: THEE NODES - ALL DAY, EVERY DAY EP
description:
Brilliant 6 track 7" EP from crazed Canadian punks THEE NODES.

Twisted Hardcore that sounds like a cross between Rudimentary Peni and Devo. Insanely catchy.

Limited to 195 copies, this has already sold out just about everywhere so don't miss your chance to pick one up while you still can.

Screen printed covers and inner sleeves and lyric insert.

name: CONTRAST ATTITUDE / SEE YOU IN HELL - SPLIT EP (ORANGE VINYL)
description:
Limited repress of this great split 7" between two stalwarts of the hardcore punk scene.

It's a good match up as both bands play blazing fast hardcore and the packaging is amazing with artwork by Murillo that's up there with his best work in my opinion.

2 tracks from each band. Unique to this split.

This is pressed on clear orange vinyl, looks great.

name: CONTRAST ATTITUDE - BLACK AND WHITE EP
description:
Euro pressing of this killer 4 track EP, presented with different cover artwork this time, which is arguably better than the original.

CONTRAST ATTITUDE have been consistently banging out the DISCHARGE meets DISCLOSE style hardcore for many years now and seem to get better with each release.

The energy, tightness and power they bring sets them apart in this field though, and produces a sound all of their own.

name: WARHEAD - NEVER GIVE UP LP
description:
22 tracks of raging Japanese HC Punk!

WARHEAD have been around since the early 90's and produced some of the most ferocious hardcore of that era.

Subsequently, their singles have all become quite hard to find and expensive to buy, even the represses.

Well they're all on here on one beautifully packaged LP with stunning artwork from Japanese artist SUGI.

Contains their first 7" 'Cry Of The Truth',
Second 7" 'The Lost Self And The Beating Heart',
tracks from the awesome 'Hardcore Ball 3' compilation,
tracks from the rare compilation LP 'One Shot One Kill',
Third 7" 'Drive It In Your Head',
and their rare split 7" with ORdER

If you're a fan of Japanese Hardcore then this is a total must-have.

name: ORIGIN OF M - STRUGGLE 12"
description:
10 track 12" from Japanese HC Punks ORIGIN OF M.

Featuring members of bands such as GUDON, CAVEMEN, ASPHALT etc.

It's no surprise that this is good with that pedigree but honestly, I was surprised just HOW good this was!

I'd heard ORIGIN OF M previously on compilations and liked them, its just not a band that ever stood out for me.

Until this release.....this is superb!

So good it got back to back plays ahead of a mountain of other stuff stacked up here.

I found myself actually dancing (kind of) to this involuntarily.

Miles ahead of any of their previous recordings, recommended.

name: GASMASK TERROR - COMPLETE RECORDINGS 2004-2010 CD
description:
41 track collection of everything this French HC / D-Beat band put out in a 6 year period.

Above average stuff here, this band just got better and better as they went on.
	               
Contains the Black Sun / Fake Gold LP, Architects Of Death EP, their S/T LP & 7" plus the Ruins... And Then? Demo.

Comes with booklet cover containing lyrics to nearly all tracks.

name: V/A - GET BACK OUR FUTURE -  CD (DEATH DUST EXTRACTOR / SKIZOPHRENIA / MASSGRAVE + MORE)
description:
Awesome 9 band compilation of Tsuyama City punk bands.

'TSUYAMA CITY PUNK OMNIBUS'

Each band provides two songs each. Making 19 in total..What? I can't add up? 
Aha! That's coz there's 'secret tracks' at the end of the disc :)
Hmmm.....I wonder what it could be eh?

Some seriously great stuff on this comp, it more than lives up to my expectations! Even the two bands i'd never heard before here (Obstinancy + 32x38) both did the trick.

Bands include: 
THE RUSTED / LAST / OBSTINANCY / STICKYS / 32x38/ BLACK HUMOUR CONTROL / DEATH DUST EXTRACTOR / MASSGRAVE / SKIZOPHRENIA

Some old, some new, a good mix throughout.

You cannot fail with this one.

PLEASE NOTE I SHIP ANYWHERE IN THE WORLD TO IF YOUR COUNTRY IS NOT LISTED, PLEASE CONTACT ME TO ARRANGE FOR SHIPPING.

name: MASSGRAVE / SUFFERING MIND - SPLIT 9" WITH DVD
description:
RESTOCK COMING SOON!!!!!

9 track split 9" that comes with a bonus DVD placed strategically on the back cover in its own sleeve.

This is grind / HC of the highest order, definitely the best stuff i've ever heard from Canada's MASSGRAVE. 

Poland's SUFFERING MIND had a lot to live up to in order to match the technical power and sheer violence of the MASSGRAVE side and they come a close second in my opinion. Again, top notch stuff.

This is getting some serious rotation right now, best grind split i've heard in ages.

Artwork is killer too. Lyrics are placed on the reverse of the sleeve.

Limited to 403 copies.

The DVD is a full live set from each band from 2012 and is excellent footage. Quality is super professional!

Very limited stock available.

PLEASE NOTE I SHIP ANYWHERE IN THE WORLD TO IF YOUR COUNTRY IS NOT LISTED, PLEASE CONTACT ME TO ARRANGE FOR SHIPPING.

name: PHOBIA / SUFFERING MIND - SPLIT 5" (YELLOW VINYL)
description:
RESTOCK COMING SOON!!!!!

Two monstrous legends of the grind scene combine to make a small compact 5" that equates to musical semtex, minute but explosive.

Artwork is amazing on this and the yellow vinyl disc comes housed inside a CD sized gatefold sleeve with lyrics for both bands.

Limited to 494 copies.

name: AGATHOCLES / KURWS - SPLIT 5"
description:
4 tracks from Belgian mincecore veterans AGATHOCLES and one insane track from Poland's KURWS.

CD sized cover with a fold-out booklet with collages in colour and an extensive quotation by Erich Fromm.

Limited to 483 copies.

name: NUNSLAUGHTER - WAITING TO KILL CHRIST CASSETTE LP
description:
Official cassette release of the infamous rehearsal recording from 2001.

Contains the Hate Your God demo and several bonus unreleased tracks from the same session.

24 tracks of blasphemous Death Metal.

Not many of these cassettes are available now so grab these last copies while you can.

PLEASE NOTE I SHIP ANYWHERE IN THE WORLD TO IF YOUR COUNTRY IS NOT LISTED, PLEASE CONTACT ME TO ARRANGE FOR SHIPPING.

name: THE NEFARIOUS INTEGRATION - ARTICLES OF EXECUTION 7" EP
description:
4 raw trax of corrosive thrashing death, breathing stench from the sewers of Rotterdam. Artwork by Nabbe The Bastard (Skullhog, Blind To Faith etc). 

4 track debut 7” from this Dutch HC / Crust three piece band. Their sound is described as thrash / metal / crust / punk etc.  Without those pigeon holes, I’d just put this down as hardcore / crust record myself. There are elements of thrash to the riffs on here and the vocals are really crusty in that gravel soaked style, the drums are pounded to bits on all songs, fast paced punk vibes going on from start to finish. This is not your average plodding / epic crust record, I really like this. I’m sure people would flock to this if it was a bigger name making these songs. I tried to think of bands as comparisons but came up short, it sounds like a bunch of Swedish Crust HC bands to me but there’s sharpness about these songs that really gives them a punk edge. Good stuff.

Limited pressing of 200 copies on black vinyl

name: SILENT SCREAM - PUBLIC EXECUTION LP
description:
11 track LP from Finnish Death Punks SILENT SCREAM.

This is the ghost of early KILLING JOKE reborn in Helsinki.

A lot of bands get compared to KJ but SILENT SCREAM have nailed that unique sound with tribal drum beats and echoed vocals creating a dark and sinister sound-scape.

They've also been likened to AMEBIX and I can hear that on some of these tracks too.

This is a great LP and one of my favourite listens in many a month.

Highly recommended release.

name: THE BREED - ZED' LP - RED / BLACK SPLATTER VINYL
description:
12 track LP from Czech HC Punks THE BREED.

Ripping Hardcore thrash tinged punk with a crust undertone.

Great guitars on this LP, all tracks blaze on here, there's no chugga chugga plodders.

Great political lyrics too.

This LP has an original sound, mixing several elements and managing to sound in places like BROKEN BONES, ENGLISH DOGS, DEZERTER, MASS GENOCIDE PROCESS although maybe each pair of ears that hears this will find something different within.

The artwork is stunning and really stands out on the front and back cover.
This is pressed on Black / Red swirl vinyl.

PLEASE NOTE I SHIP ANYWHERE IN THE WORLD TO IF YOUR COUNTRY IS NOT LISTED, PLEASE CONTACT ME TO ARRANGE FOR SHIPPING.

name: YOUR WAR ZINE #12 W/ VAGINORS, ABSURD SOCIETY, STOIC VIOLENCE + MORE
description:
Brand new issue of YOUR WAR.

This one features interviews with:
VAGINORS (Austraila), ABSURD SOCIETY (Japan), STOIC VIOLENCE (USA) 

Plus a rarities feature and column written by yours truly and some reviews also.

Tidy little package, as always, limited to 100 copies worldwide.

Move quick to snag one as these always go fast.

name: UNHOLY GRAVE - GRIND ANARCHY EP (RED VINYL)
description:
Killer new 6 track EP from these Japanese Grind legends.

This is the best stuff i've heard from them in years, dare I say they get better with age?

This is more raw punk than full on grind and is so much better for it.

The packaging is exceptional, housed in a thick gate-fold sleeve with lyrics, artwork + sticker.

This version is pressed on clear red vinyl.

PLEASE NOTE I SHIP ANYWHERE IN THE WORLD TO IF YOUR COUNTRY IS NOT LISTED, PLEASE CONTACT ME TO ARRANGE FOR SHIPPING.

name: SEKIEN - CRIME AND PUNISHMENT DEMO CDR
description:
4 track demo from this outstanding new band from Himeji City, Japan. 
The band describe themselves as ‘Neo-Crust’, but this is some blazing, noisy but well structured hardcore punk. 
All four tracks on here are packed with passion and anger. 
They remind me of a cross between Sunya, Crude and later era Total Noise Accord. 
The packaging for this demo is amazing. It's housed inside an oversized printed woven patch cloth sleeve with inserts and is impressive to look at. 
I highly recommend to pick one of these babies up while they last.

name: SEKIEN / VICTIMS - SPLIT CDR W/PATCH
description:
Killer split here between new hardcore punks Sekien and older pogo punks Victims. 
Sekien’s tracks totally destroy on this split.
The two songs blend into one another and create over 5 minutes of driving hardcore rage and destruction. 
Victims who hail from Osaka, produce two great tracks of their own and play spikes and studs punk rock. 
Super catchy pogo tunes with a hard edge to them. 
For a CDR the packaging is impressive and each copy comes with a Sekien patch. 
Full colour artwork on the Victims side too. 
Get this while you still can.

name: ESPERANZA - THE BEGINING CDEP
description:
4 track debut CD EP from Japanese Hardcore Punks ESPERANZA.
Formed from the ashes of one of the best Japanese Punk bands in many years, PERSEVERE, ESPERANZA play a similar style of punk.

Fast, abrasive and full of spikes, studs and snot.

For fans of VENDETTA, LAST SURVIVORS and of course PERSEVERE!!

name: TERMINUS - GRAVEYARD OF DREAMS CD
description:
19 track CD compiling all single tracks from this excellent 90' UK Anarcho Punk band.
Often forgotten and overlooked, even when they were in existence, this is one seriously underrated band.
Perhaps because they didn't have the same visual impact of bands like CONFLICT or OI POLLOI back then or perhaps because musically, they were very diverse and unique sounding compared to a lot of Anarcho bands of the time.
I was always a huge fan and whilst I own all of these singles, this compilation still excites me and in my view, this release is well warranted and a great collection of some of their best songs.
For the uninitiated, they used to be compared to a cross between MOTORHEAD and HAWKWIND but personally I always thought that they sounded like a faster version of THE MOB or a less crusty COITUS.
Brilliant song writing and addictive hooks, mixing power and politics in equal measure.
Some of these songs are absolute classics 'Violent Resistance', 'Into The Flames', 'We're Dreaming' and 'A New Tomorrow' will be in your head for weeks after playing this. In fact, I don't think I can find a dud track on this collection.

Highly recommended.

name: INSTINCT OF SURVIVAL - LAPSED INTO ABSURDITY FLEXI 7"
description:
3 track flexi from Crust Punks INSTINCT OF SURVIVAL.

A slight change in sound on this release that gives it a 90's UK Crust feel with an Anarcho edge.

Really good stuff. This is more punk than crust that's for sure.

These come in either red or green covers - I have both - and is limited to 300 copies only.

Limited stock available so don't sleep.

name: AUTONOMIA / DECLINIO SOCIAL - SPLIT 7"
description:
Great Latin HC from both bands here.

This is a multi-label release between 12 labels and the ones i do know here are more than worthy of your support.

I can see why so many different labels decided to get involved and put this EP out as it's really top notch stuff.

AUTONOMIA have been going since 1989 and hail from Lima, Peru.
They play super catchy, tight as hell anarcho HC with superb guitar work.
DECLINIO SOCIAL back them up on side B with two tracks in a similar style but with a slightly harsher production. They've been described as sounding like AUS ROTTEN but i'm not hearing that, although the comparisons with SIN DIOS and HOMOMILITIA are more warranted.

For me, this is worth it for the AUTONOMIA side alone as that's just fantastic but both bands produce great work on this 7"

The cover artwork is brilliant and was created by Japanese artist Shinshuke. All topped off with a lovely gloss finish that gives the release a feel of real quality and attention to detail.

Grab this.

name: LIFE CHAIN - UNIFORMED COWARDS 7" EP - CLEAR VINYL
description:
NEW RELEASE FROM IMMINENT DESTRUCTION RECORDS!

Co- released with ADELANTE records.

5 track debut 7" from Canada's LIFE CHAIN.

Those that caught on to this bands great demo tape released last year will know what to expect here and will surely not be disappointed.

5 new tracks of chaotic D-Beat HC, soaked in reverb and distortion, with sussed, political lyrics.

Housed in silk screened sleeves of varying colours and accompanied by a screened poster.

Clear vinyl edition.

name: LIFE CHAIN - UNIFORMED COWARDS 7" EP
description:
NEW RELEASE FROM IMMINENT DESTRUCTION RECORDS!

Co- released with ADELANTE records.

5 track debut 7" from Canada's LIFE CHAIN.

Those that caught on to this bands great demo tape released last year will know what to expect here and will surely not be disappointed.

5 new tracks of chaotic D-Beat HC, soaked in reverb and distortion, with sussed, political lyrics.

Housed in silk screened sleeves of varying colours and accompanied by a screened poster.

Black vinyl edition.

PLEASE NOTE I SHIP ANYWHERE IN THE WORLD TO IF YOUR COUNTRY IS NOT LISTED, PLEASE CONTACT ME TO ARRANGE FOR SHIPPING.

name: RAD - THIS IS RAD 7" + LOUD & FAST LP TAPE LTD 50 ONLY
description:
OFFICIALLY AUTHORISED BY THE BAND, THIS CASSETTE TAPE FEATURES ALL 27 SONGS FROM THEIR 'THIS IS RAD' 7" (NOW COMPLETELY SOLD OUT) AND THEIR TRULY AMAZING 'LOUD & FAST' LP.
THIS IS A PRO-COPIED CASSETTE STRAIGHT FROM THE BANDS' MASTERS.

IT ALSO COMES WITH AN EXCLUSIVE RAD BADGE!

HAND NUMBERED AND LIMITED TO JUST 50 COPIES.

name: V/A - MONOMANIAC VOLUME TWO + THREE LP
description:
19 track compilation LP, following on from the excellent Volume One that was released on 7" 
This encompasses both volume two and three on one 12"format.

Like with the first compilation, the artwork is seriously impressive and the variety and innovation of the bands involved is highly welcomed.

Bands involved this time around include:
BLACK HOLE OF CALCUTTA / WITCHRIST / DEPHOSPHORUS / WAKE / MUTANT SUPREMACY / WEREGOAT  / NECROSADIST / GODS OF CHAOS / BURIAL HORDES / SKULLSHITTER / HAAPOJA / NOCTURNAL VOMIT and more...

In keeping with the compilation series, all songs are around the minute mark and are provided by bands from all corners of the globe.

Recommended.

Very limited stock available.

name: BOMBANGREPP - FORRADD AV SAMHELLET 7"
description:
RE-STOCKED!!!

9 track debut EP from Swedish Raw Punks BOMBANGREPP.

Total Kang fury!!!!

Super raw and fast as lightning, like a mix of TOTALITAR & RAW HATE.

name: BRUTOPIA / LAHDON AIKA - SPLIT 7"
description:
Devastating blasts of Finnish HC from both bands on this split EP.

3 songs from Brutopia and 2 songs from Lähdön Aika.

Both bands cover a track of each others in that time honoroed tradition.

Limited stock available.

name: MUTANT SUPREMACY - ROTTING SEASON 7" EP
description:
4 tracks of crushing Death Metal from USA's MUTANT SUPREMACY.

The closet thing to BOLT THROWER in current existence.

This is superb.

Limited to 300 copies and hand numbered.

Limited stock available.

name: V/A - MONOMANIACS VOLUME ONE 7"
description:
10 bands and 12 tracks on this innovative compilation EP.

The packaging is first rate on this 7", it looks great.
Nearly all tracks are around the minute mark or less, making this a diverse mix of Hardcore, Grind, Black Metal, Noisepunk
A short & sweet blast of a comp.

Bands include SEPT STAR SEPT / DETROIT / HEAD CLEANER / DIOLCETIAN / THE HOWLING WIND and more..

This is worth it for THE HOWLING WIND track alone in my opinion, it's one of the best pieces of music i've heard all year.

Limited stock available.

name: ROCKET - GALLERIA 7"
description:
Debut 7" from this brand new band out of Tokyo.

This band has some serious pedigree though, not only do they share family relations with members of LIFE and ASSFORT, on this 7" they're joined by members of JABARA, CHEERIO, DISKRIMINADOS, VIVISICK, VERHAIZ and more...
Hardcore Family!!!   

This is an anti-war themed release and although the A-side 'Galleria' is a total HC ripper, the B-side 'Never Forget It' is much more complex musically and deep lyrically. It focuses on the deaths of the vocalist's relatives in World War II, in a place called Leyte Island, I assume when allied forces were invading..

Both songs are great in their own different ways.

Limited edition Japanese import.

Get this while you can.

name: ZYANOSE - WHY THERE GRIEVE? LP
description:
Brand new LP from Japanese Hardcore Noise Crusters ZYANOSE.

12 tracks of astonishing power.

Unbridled anger and fury channelled through total distortion and seriously addictive punk riffs.

Very limited stock available.

name: BELGRADO - SIGLO XXI LP
description:
2nd full length LP from this amazingly good band out of Barcelona.

They had a tough task to better their debut LP but managed it with this release.

11 new tracks in their distinctive anarcho / post-punk stlye.

Very limited stock available.

name: WARVICTIMS - 4 TRACK EP (GOLD COVER)
description:
New release from IMMINENT DESTRUCTION RECORDS!

4 killer blasts of hardcore punk from Sweden's D-Beat masters WARVICTIMS.

The 2 tracks on side A are unreleased recordings from the session that took place for their split 12" with FLYBLOWN and are both absolute stormers that match up against anything from that release.

2 brand new recordings on side B; including a remixed version of 'Smittbararna' (mastered by Yeap of KROMOSOM) and the best DISCLOSE cover you're ever likely to hear. 
In my opinion, it surpasses the original!

300 total pressing, with silk screened double sided covers and sticker, 150 printed in red and 150 printed in gold.

Each looks stunning so take your pick or go nuts and choose both!

name: PROXY - POLICE CAR 7"
description:
Brand new release from PROXY!!

I can hardly contain myself...!

A re-recorded version of Police Car from their demo and two new tracks that show the progress made by this excellent band since their last platter.

A band that just gets better each time you hear them.

Grab this quick while stocks last.

name: BELGRADO - S/T LP
description:
Brilliant 10 track LP from Barcelona Anarcho Punks BELGRADO.

One of my favourite bands not just now but in the past 20 years and undoubtedly one of the best around today.

Every song on this LP is wonderful. A perfect example of how passion for punk can be channelled into something melodic instead of total noise / rage and yet still be powerful enough to affect you and your way of thinking.

Destined to become a classic LP.

Fans of BELLICOSE MINDS, SCEPTRES, CRIMSON SCARLET, POST REGIMENT etc. will love this.

Highly recommended.

name: YOUR WAR ZINE #11
description:
Brand new issue of this ongoing DIY zine from USA.

This issue contains interviews with MASS POLLUTION and KROMOSOM.

As well as a rarities feature on classic Japanese 7" compiled by yours truly and the usual reviews from myself and Chris Stahlman.

name: ANGER BURNING / LIVET SOM INSATS - SPLIT 7"
description:
Swedish raw punk assault from ANGER BURNING & LIVET SOM INSATS. 
ANGER BURNING continue where they left off on their excellent 'WHEN' 12"
Here they produce another 3 tracks which will blow lovers of the D-Beat away.
LSI play raw grindcore. brutal, on point, lightning fast and loud. 
400 copies in black vinyl.

name: REDNECKS - KEEPSAKES EP
description:
4th release by Japanese HC maniacs REDNECKS.

This is possibly their best yet..

Their last EP on Hardcore Survives was great and the split with JOHNS TOWN ALOHA is probably my favourite release of theirs but this matches up to any of their previous material.

This had me hooked after 20 seconds of the first track and there is literally no let up on either side of this 7"

They've adapted their style from the crasher crust noise they began with in their early years to refine the anger and create blazing hardcore in the classic Japanese style.

This is just a total ripper and easily the best release from Hardcore Survives Records this year.

Highly recommended.

name: STATE POISON - FACK OOF FLEXI 7"
description:
2 song on-sided clear uncut flexi from Frace's premier noisemongers STATE POISON.

Both these songs pack a punch and are straight ahead no-frills punk rock.

Impossible not to enjoy.

There's a heavy Japanese HC influence on this flexi, the bass lines especially.

250 made and all sold out now so grab a copy while you can.

name: SCHIZOPHASIA - 4000 LP GREEN SWIRL VINYL (LTD 120 ONLY)
description:
Last Copies!!

Canadian noise punks return with their 4th LP '4000'

This time they return to their roots and depart from the weird psychadelic stlyes they previously used on their two 7"

This is more like their early tapes, unleashing a torrent of total noise punk in the style of CONFUSE. 
A serious comparison to make in this instance.

Side A is 5 tracks of stipped down crazed and vioent, angry punk chaos that brings to mind DISORDER at their noisiest.
On Side B they crank up the intensity to unprecedented levels with 10 track of utter sonic mayhem.
This is definitely a noise to get glued by.......

This version is pressed on green swirled vinyl and is limited to 120 copies only. 
Very limited stock available so act fast.

name: YOUR WAR ZINE #10
description:

Also contains rants and reviews from yours truly...

name: POIKKEUS - KATSMESSER 7" (CRUST WAR RECORDS)
description:
LONG awaited follow up to their classic and highly sought after 1st EP, POIKKEUS return out of nowhere with another brilliant release.

Where as earlier in the bands history, they played some killer Finnish HC style, this is rougher and tougher and shows they've matured well.

I think I prefer this POIKKEUS, but maybe that's because I played their last 7" to death. There's still flashes of the old style of course but this is excellent stuff that's drawn comparisons with other Japanese greats like GISM and ZOUO.

Nice packaging too.
This is one of the best Japanese bands, effortlessly cool...

name: INFERNOH - 7 SPAR 12"

description:
Raw Hardcore from Vancouver B.C with a solid D-Beat backbone that doesn’t bore you to tears. Searing guitar work and a vocalist that can actually manage to convey his live frustration through recorded media, a rare feat. A distinct sound is hard to pinpoint. Influences range all over the place from Death Side to Poison Idea. Everyone will tell you something different, make your own judgement.

Recommended release. These guys rip it up!

name: VOCO PROTESTA - NENIAM KONFIDU AL LA STATO LP
description:
Tokyo's VOCO PROTESTA second LP finally arrives.
When they started out they're sound was harsh blown out distortion, similar to Disclose or Ferocious X but their new twelve track LP brings to mind early 80's Swedish hardcore bands such as CRUDE SS or SVART PARAD as well as Italian / Spanish anarchist bands from the same period like IV REICH / WRETCHED. All ran through their own Japanese filter and with a crystal clear recording. 
Sang integrally in Esperanto with a strong anarchist message "Neniam Konfidu to the Stato" (Never trust the State) is a statement against the fresh hope stale world we live in.

name: PANDEMIA - MODERN PLAGUE LP
description:
NEW RELEASE ON IMMINENT DESTRUCTION RECORDS!

10 track debut LP from Greek Punks PANDEMIA.

Heavily involved in the Greek DIY scene and active politically, these sentiments are powerfully evident in the music they create.

They produce a classic 80's anarcho sound that's mixed with some post punk elements.

Comparisons could be made to bands such as CONFLICT, VEX, FLUX OF PINK INDIANS, LACK OF KNOWLEDGE, THE SYSTEM,     EX-HUMANS, REALITY CONTROL, STRESS, LIBERTY etc.
But they still have their own refreshing, passionate sound and the production on this LP suits them perfectly.

Sometimes fast and aggressive, sometimes slow, dark and haunting but always angry and sincere.

This is a future classic that epitomises the ideology and spirit of Anarcho Punk.

name: DISPAIR - HEADING FOR THE VOID LP
description:
14 tracks of outstanding D-Beat from Finland!
New bands featuring members of VIIMEINEN KOLONNA.
Blown out and distorted but not so that it's unlistenable.
This is still super catchy hardcore punk that makes me feel like spraying beer in my face while shouting loudly and smashing the tin off the nearest wall.
Obvious DISCHARGE influence but it's circa 'Fight Back' era and just makes this even more raw and dirty.
One of the best records in this style i've heard in a long time.
Totally addictive.
Comes with sew on patch and is limited to 400 copies only.

name: FALSE INSIGHT / SBGM - NEW SCUM CITY EP 7"
description:
Awesome split 7" from Japanese stench crusters FALSE INSIGHT and veteran hardcore punks SBGM (Stupid Babies Go Mad).
This is the first outing for FALSE INSIGHT and SBGM pull out the best stuff I have ever heard from them on this 7" another band that has improved with age!


Comes with printed black & white OBI strip, hand numbered and limited to 500 copies only.
Already sold out in Japan, this went in a matter of days!
The third release, put out simultaneously from STRONG MIND RECORDS.
Limited stock available so snap it up now while you still can.
Japanese Import

name: ABSURD SOCIETY - S/T 7"
description:
Killer 4 track debut EP from Japanese Crust Punks ABSURD SOCIETY.

After 2 well received demos, the band finally lay down their first vinyl offering.
Fans of SDS, HAKUCHI, ANTISECT, etc. will relish this.

Brilliant cover art by Mid (DEVIATED INSTINCT) tops off a beautiful package with printed red OBI strip, hand numbered and limited to 500 copies only.
Already sold out in Japan, this went in a matter of days!
The first release from STRONG MIND RECORDS.
Destined to be a collectors item in the years to come so snap it up now while you still can.
Japanese Import.

name: ULSTER - '95-'96 EP
description:
From the same scene that unleashed monsters like OLHO SECO, HINO MORTAL and BRIGADA DO ODIO, the noise-punk masked legends are back with an unreleased recording of loud, visceral and extreme punk dating from 1995-96! 
Three of the four former members from 1979-82 in a session that captures the essence of the band aggressiveness. Influenced by the Irish militia brutality and influencing the own TERRÖTTEN label name with their ULSTERROR, ULSTER is back to terrorize and crush the ignorant!!

http://youtu.be/mOvexRkxwDw

name: PROXY - SOMETHING WE'VE ALL SEEN BEFORE LP
description:
At last! The début vinyl offering from Montreal's finest, PROXY.
Co-released between IMMINENT DESTRUCTION RECORDS and INFLAMMABLE MATERIAL RECORDS.
7 tracks of pure punk rock that draws influences from classic UK punk like BLITZ or THE PARTISANS and but underpins it with the steel of early MOTORHEAD / GBH/ TOXIC REASONS.
Timeless catchy but equally powerful modern Punk from ex-members of INEPSY and KONTEMPT. 
Full colour jackets with double sided lyric inner sleeve, pressed on 150 gram red vinyl.

name: TOTAL WAR - 8 TRACK DEMO EP
description:
This demo blew me away when I heard it last year and thankfully GASMASK RECORDS have given it a vinyl pressing.

8 tracks (at the title suggests) of relentless, raging hardcore punk.

Fans of FRAMTID, PERDITION, HELLKRUSHER, DISCLOSE will lap this up.

Limited stock available.

name: GADGIE ZINE #29
description:
Consistently excellent UK zine packed with humorous columns and some varied punk reviews.

A really enjoyable read, nice one!

PLEASE DO NOT ORDER WITH 7" AS THIS WILL NOT FIT INSIDE A 7" PACKET. ORDER SEPARATELY OR WITH 12"!

name: AGGRASTAT - NOISE EXTERMINATION EP (LTD YELLOW VINYL)
description:
New release from IMMINENT DESTRUCTION RECORDS!

Debut 6 track EP from AGGRASTAT.

Total noise damage!!!

Cover art by SUGI.

Lovers of CONFUSE / ZYANOSE / ATROCIOUS MADNESS take note.

Limited copies available on ultra limited yellow vinyl.
Exclusive colour! Last copies available! Act fast!!

name: V/A - SKITLIV! 2 X CD SWEDISH HARDCORE COMPILATION
description:
38 tracks of pure KANG! On 2 discs.

Bands include DISFEAR / WARCOLLAPSE / VICTIMS / ANTI - CIMEX / WOLFBRIGADE / UNCURBED / ANGER BURNING / KVOTERINGEN / MOB 47 / GIFTGASATTACK / KRIGSHOT / DRILLER KILLER / ROVSVETT / MEANWHILE and loads more....

Comes in a digi-pack with booklet.

Outstanding compilation..

name: SELVFORAKT- OUTRO DIA, OUTRA CAÇA 7"
description:
4 tracks, a few years ago Terrötten sealed an international friendship releasing the split with Brazilian finest DISARM and Norwegian SOUND YOUR ALARM. 
Now, three years later, these maniacs decided to join forces and set up a project arising from the confines of hell: SELVFORAKT! Two Brazilian guys and a singer from Black Metal homeland with the best Raw Crust with gruff metallic leads! 
Four malevolent hymns with a vocalist who sounds like Cerberus leading a wolf-pack from hell that will wash the humanity from their addictions! 
Apocalyptic Crust for fans of DOOM, NAUSEA, MISERY, ANTI-CIMEX and WARCOLLAPSE!

name: KVOTERINGEN - SAMHALLETS FORRADARE CD
description:
CD collection containing all track from the "Samhallets Forradare" LP, the "Dodens Handslag" 7", and the split with Nitad. Killer swedish punk.

Kvoteringen is a Swedish punk rock band formed 2003 in Örebro. The band plays a style of Scandinavian D-beat and hardcore punk. Members are Jallo-guitar & bass, Fredrik Larzon-drums and Calle-vocals. The band share members with Meanwhile, Ääritila, Totalitär, No Security, Skitslakt, Dischange among others....

20 tracks of pure Kang!!!

name: UNIDOS PELO ODIO - RENASCENDO DAS CINZAS CD
description:
Long running Porto Alegre, Brazil, powerful punk/hardcore gets their 1st full-length release out after 12 years! 
If you are into powerful and fast hardcore with pulverizing Brazilian-punk styled vocals, D-beat+roll flavored guitars, Crusty bass lines (Gustavo from Gritos de Alerta) and earthquake beats, you will love UNIDOS PELO ODIO. 
Their 21 songs range from the modern crust / HC to punk rock going to d-beat and thrash in a top quality record session with more than 60 mins of power!

name: DEATH DEALERS - FLIES OF ATROCITY CD
description:
Death Dealers is a Raw Crust D-beat band featuring Dean Jones, Phil Vane and Chino from Extreme Noise Terror and Charlie Claeson from Anti-Cimex alongside members of Raw Noise!
Pure hardcore annihilation done by guys who have been playing punk for more than 20 years. 

Artwork & design by Sean Fitzgerald. Deluxe Digi-pack version. 
For fans of: Extreme Noise Terror, Anti-Cimex, Raw Noise, Discharge, Doom, Disrupt..

name: V/A - DISCHARGE TRIBUTO CD
description:
27 bands from all depths of the jungle country, within all extreme styles of music. 
The bands are: Gritos de Alerta, Living in Hell, Lobotomia, Armagedom, Skarnio, Besthoven, Scum Noise, Apokalyptic Raids, Ação Direta, Subcut, Disarm, Whipstriker, A.R.D., Nuclear Frost, Desastre, Social Chaos, Death From Above, Unfit Scum, Chaka, Murro no Olho, D-ecreasing Life, Karne Krua, Terror Revolucionário, Final Trágico,os Maltrapilhos, Escoria e Corja. Everything presented in a deluxe CD and poster-booklet with lots of information, rare Discharge photos, and even a small interview with Bones and Rat in Portuguese.

name: EXTREME NOISE TERROR - PHONOPHOBIA CD + BONUS TRACKS
description:
Originaly released in 1991, but this time remastered and remixed from the original master tapes. 
Features the classic line-up of Dean Jones, Phil Vane, Peter Hurley (Disgust), Mark Bailey and Tony "Stick" Dickens (Doom, Deviated Instinct, etc.). 
This reissue come with two unreleased bonus tracks from the same original session and a full set recorded live at Leeds in UK in 1986!

name: WHIPSTRIKER - LOUDMAN T-SHIRT
description:
I got this design exclusively made up from Victor WHIPSTIKER in a limited run of 10 shirts!

I have 5 x Large (L)+ 5 x Extra Large (XL)

Grab one while you can!

name: V/A - STEP INTO THE LIGHT LP JAPANESE PUNK COMPILATION
description:
VERY limited amount of copies of this brilliant compilation LP available for a short time!

Bands featured are:

VENDETTA / ROUGH STUFF / REJECTS / END OF SEEDS / STRANGENESS / DRUNK BOIS / SKIZOPHRENIA

This must-have for your collection comes with separate screen printed inserts for each band, a really nice touch.

Highly recommended!!!

name: LUCY & THE LIPSTIX - TIME MACHINE 7"
description:
Nice treat for the more musically educated amongst you here!

This Japanese band are hugely popular in their homeland and after hearing their LP and this 7" I can understand why.

2 tracks here that will twist your head until it snaps off.
This band are unique! So hard to describe their sound but if i tell you that CLOCKWORK KENJI from THE HAT TRICKERS had a massive input on this 7".....well, you'll be none the wiser.

This is not hardcore! This is futuristic and retro at the same time!
Expand your mind!!!

These were only available as tour editions and so are very difficult to obtain outside of Japan. (Collector Nerd Hint!)

Strictly limited to 300 copies only and most of those already gone of course.

Very limited stock!

Brand new issue of this excellent zine.
This is one of my top 3 zines in the world right now, great interviews, reviews and seriously well written articles from an editor that is heavily involved with the worldwide punk scene.

Contains interviews with DIRTY WOMBS, RAW NERVES, CUT OFF!, ZVARNA, loads of reviews, reports, articles, just a brilliant read!

description:

78:10 minutes of hardcore horror!!

name: NETJAJEV SS - ANARCHY ANDROMEDA LP
description:
NETJAJEV SOCIETY SYSTEM 'ANARCHY ANDROMEDA' LP
 
Recorded beyond the darkest reaches of space in early 2005 and 
originally released in 2008 as a limited edition of 234 copies, this 
classic slab of nether-worldly hardcore thrash has now been repressed for the bewildered Earth masses. 
Kiss all notions of rational thought goodbye and experience the brain fucking horrors of Dr. Magnus Lundberg’s sonic crimes against mankind. 
Twenty tracks of depraved 
punk violence and neuro-surgical torture including a cover of THE 
RAMONES “I Don’t Wanna Be Learned”. 
This roaring zenith in NETJAJEV SS’s storied career of interstellar blasphemy was unfortunately missed by most the first time around. 
Now is your chance to make up for lost 
abuse!

name: UNKNOWN TO GOD - S/T EP
description:
Tough, dark, and galloping hardcore that's been compared to (early) The Execute, from these Sydney veterans. 

Features ex-members of LAST CHAOS and DEATHCAGE.

This is raging hardcore pure and simple, but well above average.

A great debut, self released black vinyl 7", limited to 300 copies.

Recommended.

name: V/A - ACCELERATION TO DOOMSDAY EP
description:
New release from IMMINENT DESTRUCTION RECORDS!

Many months in the making, and after frustrating delays from the pressing plant, finally ready for release is the killer 4-way split EP 'ACCELERATION TO DOOMSDAY'

Featuring LASTLY / DISTURD / AGAINST THE GRAIN / DESPERDICIO

A Japanese Hardcore explosion!

Check here for a sample:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dVTXioSVo5s

name: SUB ALERT / ANGELPISS - SPLIT EP
description:
SUB ALERT team up with fellow Swedes ANGELPISS for this killer hardcore split EP.

Ripping kang that you know and love.

Limited stock available.

name: SUB ALERT / KRIMTANK - SPLIT EP
description:
2 absolute ragers here from Sweden.

Fast, aggressive and catchy hardcore punk played by guys who live and breathe this shit daily.

Great split.

name: TENSE REACTION - BLACK HOLE 7"
description:
8 tracks of fast and raging 80’s inspired hardcore. 
These people are old enough to know just plain copying bands of yesteryear is boring. 
So they've added enough twists to their songs to keep it interesting.
Members have been playing punk for ages in some of the better Dutch hardcore outfits like VITAMIN-X, DANDARE and ALL TENSED UP.
It shows.

name: V/A - NOISE CIRCUS FROM JAPANESE NOSE MANIACS EP
description:
4 band compilation EP.

'NOISE CIRCUS FROM JAPANESE NOSE MANIACS EP'

Pressed on green vinyl and limited to 500 copies only, sold out fast from the label.

Bands here are TANTRUM / STAGNATION / AOSTRAPOS / EXIT HOPPERS (EXIT HIPPIES)

Last available copies of this brilliant comp EP.

Don't miss this.

name: LEGIO OCCULTA - SLIME CRAWLER TAPE (LIMITED 154 ONLY)
description:
LEGIO OCCULTA - Slime Crawler - Demo MC 

Amazing atmospheric Swedish Death Metal.

I'm not a huge fan of this genre but this really hits the spot and is a really compelling listen. I have been playing this regularly and am seriously impressed with it. 

If you like stuff like SKAGOS, OEDE, AUSTRASIAN GOAT etc. then you will love this! 

Pro-printed tape that's highly recommended.

Limited to 154 copies on red cassette, all copies are hand numbered.

Last available copies! 

Sold out from the label and pretty much everywhere else now too.

name: THE CAR - ABEP CD
description:
Debut release from this Osaka 3 piece.

Originally pressed on 7" vinyl and limited to 300 copies, this sold out  in a heartbeat.

Now available again in limited quantities with different artwork.

Super catchy Japanese punk rock!

Very limited stock!

name: PEACEFUL COLLAPSE / LIFE CONSUMED - SPLIT CDR
description:
5 track crusher here from Japan's PEACEFUL COLLAPSE and LIFE CONSUMED.

Powerful Japanese Hardcore release!

Limited edition, Japanese import.

name: NU-COORDINATOR - S/T CD
description:
Debut CD EP from this extraordinary band from Tokyo!

This is future new wave!!

Imagine a mix of THE SLOWMOTIONS, early TALKING HEADS, THE FUTURES, BLACK & WHITE, OMIT VOMIT, JOYSTAX, filtering through an electronic wave of punk rock psychedelia! 

This band are amazing and although not for most of you regular noise-mongers, anyone who appreciates innovative and catchy as hell music should grab this now!

3 tracks but the last one lasts over 10 minutes so this is still a substantial listen and a fun one at that!

Very limited stock available!

Japanese import with OBI.

name: PLF / SUBCUT - SPLIT 7"
description:
After being a pipe dream since the year 2000, this split has finally been pressed onto seven deadly inches of plastic, with these two grindcore outfits each delivering their brand of angry blastage. Houston, TX's P.L.F. continue their relentless campaign of Gulf Coast Grindcore with 2 tight, thrash-grinding rippers recorded in 2010, and a cover of Terrorizer's "Human Prey". The songs fly from blast parts to d-beats to the occasional thrash metal moment to start-and-stop thrashcore and still retain a fluid sense of delivery.  
Flip the record over, and Subcut, who are from Sao Paulo, Brazil, just destroy your sensibilities, with five enraged tracks of truly excellent crusty grind that are delivered like blow after blow in the final beating of your life. Every entry in Subcut's discography, since they formed in the 90's, is comprised of nothing but the most enraged grind tracks--- virtually no metal influence here-- just disgust for the ugliness and harsh realities of life seem to fuel the onslaught: Ripping fast power chords and bass distortion, insane, fast-blast drumming not unlike Hail of Rage, and totally over-the top vocals screamed through it all. 
This is Real Grind!

name: DESOLATION - REST IN PANIC 7" LTD SPLATTER VINYL
description:
Blasting metallic hardcore fusing the melodic influence of Japanese "Burning spirits" hardcore with straight forward attack of US thrash and the dark tone of European Crust.
DESOLATION went on Hiatus shortly after their Self-tilted prank Debut LP of 2005, but return with a new vocalist and three new tracks. 
Fusing influences of the members previous and current bands-BORN/DEAD, ABRUPT, STRUNG UP, SCURVY DOGS with a marked inspiration from Japanese Hardcore with relentless upbeat energy and searing leads , these are the fastest DESOLATION tracks yet, but still retain the complex song writing and bleak feel of their previous releases.
Cover Features amazing artwork by the brilliant Japanese artist SUGI.
Limited Mail order only copies on splatter white/black vinyl.

name: VIVID SEKT 'A DECEPTION OF DESIRE 2007-2010' CD
description:
Portland's VIVID SEKT features members of similarly influenced bands ARCTIC FLOWERS and MORAL HEX but VIVID SEKT is different in that they do not retain the hardcore elements of the former nor the more new wave/post punk sounds of the later proving that
VIVID SEKT is a DIY punk band through and through.
This CD contains 12 tracks of their works from 2007-2010.
New anarcho punk classic.

name: V/A - MABUKKUASA CD -M.D.C / THE BOLLOCKS / CARBURETOR DUNG
description:
3 way split between US Hardcore legends M.D.C. (Millions Of Dead Cops) and two Malaysian punk bands that you may or may not have heard of.
CARBURETOR DUNG and THE BOLLOCKS.
Both these bands are deserving of your attention and will kick your arse big time.
THE BOLLOCKS especially show improvement here from the spiky top pogo punx into something really powerful and in your face.
14 track in all......

name: ICE NINE - NOBODY'S SON 7" LTD WHITE VINYL
description:
ICE NICE from Indianapolis, Indiana represented everything that was great about hardcore of the 1990's.
A uniquely original band that broke up before an LP had the chance to be released. 
Band members went on to play in TIME IN MALTA, BURN IT DOWN, MAHJAS, THE PROBLEMATICS, YOU WILL DIE and THE DREAM IS DEAD. 
In 2009 the band reformed with all original members to play Indianapolis's DUDEFEST.
The response was so phenomenal ICE NINE wrote 3 new tracks that pick up right where they left off.

This is the mailorder only white vinyl edition.

Limited stock!

name: ASSFORT - AKYUFUOTO EP LTD WHITE VINYL
description:
Manic Tokyo thrash-lunging straight to the jugular with vicious speed, a thrashing drum attack, insane guitar solos and coarse vocals. ASSFORT were the first classic Japanese styled hardcore band to tour in the United States, unleashing a devastating amount of high energy and flooring audiences on both coasts. They released several records, including a split with CHAOS U.K., on Vinyl Japan Records, a CD on the legendary Selfish label, an EP on the mighty Mangrove label and then two Well received follow up LP's in Japan with a new line up.
This version is pressed on limited white vinyl.

A classic EP!

name: MY TURN - ATHENS CD
description:
Positive and passionate hardcore punk from Athens.

Debut 10 track album from this cool bunch of guys heavily involved in the Greek DIY scene.

Combining great riffs, a melodic guitar sound and powerful vocals with sussed and intelligent lyrics.

Greek import!

name: FREAKS - LIVE IN VAIN CD
description:
Amazing return from these Tokyo veterans!

11 tracks of awesome Japanese hardcore punk!

This is by far the bands best material to date.

First 3 orders come with limited edition 3" badge!

One of the best releases of the year, don't pass this one up.

name: DIRTY WOMBS - WE RISE CASSETTE EP
description:
Self released 6-track EP on cassette format.
Limited to 300 copies.
Last chance to get this pressing.
Contains DEATHSIDE cover.
Recommended for fans of 'Burning Spirits' style hardcore.
DIRTY WOMBS are to feature on the upcoming international hardcore compilation LP on IMMINENT DESTRUCTION RECORDS.
Do yourself a favour and pick this up now!

name: AVFALL - DISH IT OUT EP
description:
This is 2nd ep of Tokyo young punks Avfall! 
The original singer quit and then the bass player took over vocal duty. 
This 7" was planned to be released on demo cassette, but  Hardcore Survives decided it was too good and need perssingto vinyl!
Totalitar, Fyfan and Skitkids are all influences here but this is a non-categorized hardcore attack punk!
Spat out vocals, chainsaw guitars, rumbling bass line and stop / start drumming! 
6 songs of pure hardcore punk.

Limited Stock Available!!!

name: STRANGE FACTORY - FUKUSHIMA NIGHTMARE EP
description:
Anti-Nuke and Anti-Nuclear Plant protest EP from a band who KNOWS as they are from Fukushima in Japan. 

This long awaited 2nd 7" is released after various splits and compilation appearances.
With years of practice behind them, they produce a ferocious Avskum style D-beat raw punk noise attack!
Absurdity, anger and sadness. 
This band are not posers this is real rebel music.
Lyrics and great artwork are included.
It's no TV sketch!

name: CHEERIO - CIU TOMORROW 7"
description:
Debut 4 track 7" of brilliant hardcore from this band making a BIG splash over in Japan right now (check out the twin vocalists, you'll get the joke)
These guys have been compared to GAUZE for their intensity. 
Add in a dose of PAINTBOX style psychedelia and you are getting nearer their sound. 
Ex-members of NO THINK and STRUCK.
This will be your new favourite band!

Limited stock available so be quick!

name: GIFTGASATTACK - DEADLY FUTURE FLEXI 7"
description:
Four ultra raw studio tracks recorded back in 2009. Different versions of these songs later appeared on the Noise Hero 12", but this noise-drenched session is previously unreleased.
Limited to 400 copies on double-sided orange flexis in picture sleeve with additional insert.

name: GASMIASMA- CRASHERMANGLE 7"
description:
Killer 4 track EP from this LA band.

Hand numbered and limited to 500 copies only with silk screened covers.

Comparisons have been made to Doom and that's not far off the mark.

This will pummel you into submission!

Crusty hardcore punk featuring members of Hellkontroll, Crowbar, Down & Psychon Vex

Very Limited Stock!

name: CITIZEN FISH - DANCING ON SPIKES CD
description:
New release on BLUURG RECORDS!
6 new tracks from Anarcho Ska Punk veterans CITIZEN FISH
CD comes in a digi-pack with artwork, fold out poster & lyrics.
Still producing great songs after all these years.

name: PERMACULTURE - SWALLOW WHAT YOU'RE GIVEN EP
description:
4 tracks of perfect Anarcho Punk, comparable to later era Crass, A-Heads, Karma Sutra, Arctic Flowers, Internal Autonomy, Contravene etc.
Features members of Nuclear Family, Social Cirkle, Confines.
This long awaited EP is as intelligent and it is catchy.
Recommended for lovers of 80's Anarcho Punk and anyone who still believes in thinking outside of this system.

name: BERSICKER / R.O.T.T.E.R Split 7"
description:
6 tracks in total of Raging D-Beat from BERSICKER (UK) and Insane Jaw-less Skull-punk from R.O.T.T.E.R (USA)

Mastered by Jack Control at Enormous Door.

Ltd run of 300 copies on black vinyl and hand numbered.

name: Alea Iacta Est / RAS - Split 7"
description:
IMMINENT DESTRUCTION RECORDS in cooperation with NHDIYST records, SEKAK records, and REST OF NOISE PRODUCTIONS have released an evil split EP from ALEA IACTA EST (Slovakia) / RAS (Spain). 13 tracks of fast grind / crust vs. Old school grind. 250 copies on black vinyl, hand numbered with black and white packaging and very limited special edition of 52 pieces on red vinyl with handmade packaging, booklets and stickers. You can find a sample of 2 songs from the EP at www.bandzone.cz / pechsekac
VERY LIMITED STOCK LEFT!!!
